article.description: Free throws lift Florida A&M past Stetson, 63-60
article.headline: Free throws lift Florida A&M past Stetson, 63-60
article.linkText: Free throws lift Florida A&M past Stetson, 63-60
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Reggie Lewis converted three straight free throws with two seconds remaining in the game to lift Florida A&M to its first win of the season, knocking off Stetson, 63-60, Thursday night. Willie Green's three-point play with 1:14 remaining pulled Stetson even at 60-60, but with time winding down Raekwon Harney fouled Lewis on an attempted 3-pointer, sending him to the free throw line. Jamie Adams scored 23 points on 7-of-10 shooting from the field to lead the Rattlers (1-2). Lewis added another 14 points, including converting 4 of 5 shots from the free throw line. Trailing by nine at halftime, Stetson got a lift from Harney, who came off the bench to score nine of his 12 points in the second half. Aaron Graham led the Hatters (0-3) with 14 points and Kentwan Smith added another 11.
